│ 6f. Security classification in src/sanitize.rs                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                               │
│ - Add "register_strategy" to SENSITIVE_TOOLS — it modifies canister state (creates templates, activates them)                                 │
│ - Do NOT add to UNTRUSTED_OUTPUT_TOOLS — the output is system-generated confirmation, not external data                                       │
│                                                                                                                                               │
│ This means the agent cannot call register_strategy immediately after http_fetch (which is untrusted). The agent must have an intermediate     │
│ non-sensitive step (like memorize or recall) between fetching an ABI and registering it. This is the right behavior — it forces the agent to  │
│ reason about the ABI before blindly registering it from an external source.                                                                   │
